This paper deals with deep learning methods for MR-to-CT synthesis, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a generative adversarial network (GAN), which is a popular deep learning technique used in many applications, including image synthesis. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves training a neural network, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves image processing, which could fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
